-# Locals: casual_name
- casual_name = local_assigns.fetch(:casual_name)

.alert.alert-light.border.mb-0
  %h3.fw-semibold.mb-2 Goal of this page
  %p.mb-3
    Find moments already in Slack about #{casual_name} and turn them into draft OGOs—without sending a feedback request for something that already happened.

  %h3.fw-semibold.mb-2 Context
  %p.mb-2
    OurGruuv Observations (OGOs) reinforce what strengthens the community and correct what harms it. Logging them is a shared responsibility:
  %p.mb-2
    If you see something that strengthens our community and aspirations and you don’t log an OGO, and it never happens again, that missed reinforcement is partly on you. If you see something that harms our aspirations and you don’t log an OGO, and it happens again, that missed correction is largely on you.
  %p.mb-3
    Slack is where many of those moments already live. This Beta flow helps you excavate them into drafts you can review and publish.

  %h3.fw-semibold.mb-2 Specifics of this page
  %p.mb-0
    Connecting Slack search and reviewing candidate moments will land in later steps. For now, use this tab to understand the intent of sourcing OGOs from Slack.
